cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.DS, cs.ST. 

The paper discusses a method for eliminating features in LASSO and other l1-penalized convex problems, which are commonly used in machine learning and data analysis. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CV (Computer Vision) as these fields heavily rely on these types of problems. The paper also mentions the potential for parallelization, which suggests a possible fit for cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.ST (Statistics).
